  "title": "AV Technician",
  "description": "<ul><li>Operation of all audio-visual equipment with the aim to provide high quality technical standards</li><li>Ensure that the audio-visual equipment is tested and in correct working order before use or an event; investigate faults and recommend further actions to rectify</li><li>Maintains audio visual equipment including routine inspections and preventative maintenance</li><li>Maintain a strong working knowledge of video and audio equipment, wireless technology, computers, projectors, and video conferencing equipment</li><li>Coordinate integration with specialty audio visual equipment as needed</li><li>Responsible for cord management & safe set up and dismantle</li><li>Liaison with project manager regarding the exact audio-visual requirements for events.</li><li>Candidates who possess Class 3 driving license will be an added advantage.</li><li>Good communications and interpersonal skills, team player with good discipline and working attitude</li></ul>",
